Use the v3 api

From your provided script and mention of using the YouTube Data API v3, it appears that you want to enhance the functionality by fetching video titles from the YouTube Data API. 

To do this, you first need to get an API key from the Google API Console and enable the YouTube Data API v3. After that, you can make requests to fetch video details such as titles.

Here's a simplified example of how to use the YouTube Data API v3 to fetch the title of a video within your existing `updateVideoTitle` function. Remember to replace `'YOUR_API_KEY'` with your actual API key:

```javascript
const API_KEY = 'YOUR_API_KEY'; // Replace with your actual API key

// ...

const updateVideoTitle = (index) => {
    const playlist = player.getPlaylist();
    if (!playlist) return;

    const videoId = playlist[index];
    if (videoId) {
        const titleDiv = document.getElementById('videoTitle');
        titleDiv.textContent = 'Loading...';

        // Fetch video details using YouTube Data API
        fetch(`https://www.googleapis.com/youtube/v3/videos?id=${videoId}&key=${API_KEY}&part=snippet`)
            .then(response => response.json())
            .then(data => {
                const videoTitle = data.items[0].snippet.title;
                titleDiv.textContent = videoTitle; // Display fetched title
            })
            .catch(error => {
                console.error('Error fetching video details:', error);
                titleDiv.textContent = 'Error loading title.';
            });
    }
};
```
With this additional code, the `updateVideoTitle` function will make a fetch request to the YouTube Data API to retrieve the video's title each time the `onPlayerReady` or `onStateChange` event is fired. 

Remember that you'll need to handle API rate limits and errors properly in a production environment to ensure a smooth user experience.

Finally, to use the YouTube Data API, you'll need to comply with YouTube's terms of service and handle user data according to their guidelines, as well as provide proper attribution when displaying video information.

